{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769619020,"nonce":"fM+gnuRNNZASOnb6IKeYmkji26I=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mdDDi","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/98","origin":"github"},"title":"Make sync-repos workflow discoverable to AI agents","message":"## Problem\n\nThe sync repos workflow was implemented in PR #62 but is not discoverable by AI agents:\n\n- ✅ **Script exists**: `.agent/scripts/sync_repos.py`\n- ✅ **Workflow doc exists**: `.agent/workflows/ops/sync-repos.md`\n- ❌ **No Makefile target**: `make sync` doesn't work\n- ❌ **Not in CLI_COMMANDS.md**: No `/sync-repos` entry for discoverability\n- ❌ **Not in quickstart**: Not mentioned in AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md\n\n## User Impact\n\nWhen asked to \"sync repos\", AI agents:\n1. Try `make sync` → fails\n2. Check CLI_COMMANDS.md → not listed\n3. Fall back to basic `vcs pull workspaces/` (doesn't respect dirty repos or feature branches)\n\nThe smart sync logic in `sync_repos.py` is bypassed entirely.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n1. **Add Makefile target**:\n   ```makefile\n   sync:\n       @python3 .agent/scripts/sync_repos.py\n   ```\n\n2. **Add to CLI_COMMANDS.md** under \"Development Commands\":\n   ```markdown\n   ### `/sync-repos`\n   \n   **File**: `.agent/workflows/ops/sync-repos.md`\n   **Script**: `.agent/scripts/sync_repos.py`\n   \n   **What it does**:\n   - Safely syncs all workspace repositories\n   - Pulls on main/jazzy/rolling branches\n   - Only fetches on feature branches\n   - Skips dirty repos to prevent conflicts\n   \n   **Example**:\n   ```bash\n   # Dry run\n   python3 .agent/scripts/sync_repos.py --dry-run\n   \n   # Execute\n   make sync\n   ```\n   ```\n\n3. **Update AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md**: Mention syncing as a common operation\n\n## Related\n\n- Original implementation: #61, PR #62\n- Fixes to sync_repos.py: PR #64, PR #71\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`","files":null}]}